From: enfs-dkms
Subject: [PATCH] net/sunrpc/Kconfig: add CONFIG_SUNRPC_ENFS

The SUNRPC_ENFS gate compiles sunrpc_enfs_adapter.o (multipath_ops
registry) into sunrpc.ko. enfs.ko's Kconfig (`config ENFS`)
`select`s this so it auto-enables.

---
 net/sunrpc/Kconfig | 12 ++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 12 insertions(+)

--- a/net/sunrpc/Kconfig
+++ b/net/sunrpc/Kconfig
@@ -129,3 +129,15 @@ config SUNRPC_XPRT_RDMA

 	  If unsure, or you know there is no RDMA capability on your
 	  hardware platform, say N.
+
+config SUNRPC_ENFS
+	bool "sunrpc support ENFS"
+	depends on SUNRPC
+	depends on X86 || X86_64 || ARM64
+	default n
+	help
+	 This option enables support multipath of the NFS protocol
+	 in the kernel's NFS client.
+	 This feature will improve performance and reliability.
+
+	 If sure, say Y.
